column9:
Well, it's time for me to express my opinion on Postal III. Here's what I can say about the game in a nutshell:

A laggy, buggy mess.
As a fan of the first two games, I was shocked by the quality of this product. Optimization? No, never heard of it. The missions are a complete nightmare, riddled with bugs.

Pros:
- There are two paths to progress: complete the game without killing anyone or destroying everyone and everything;
- A couple of decent missions.

Cons:
- Optimization;
- Bugs;
- Stupid jokes;
- Broken NPCs;
- Frequent crashes;
- Most missions are terrible;
- It's too quick to complete.

I wanted to give the game a chance, buying it after a long time, thinking I was wrong and that there were some good moments. Yes, there were some, but they were few and far between, and that doesn't save the game. I do not recommend either purchasing or playing.

So, my opinion of this game is quite mixed, and here's why:

Pros:
- Postal 3 is just as trashy, dark humorous, and immoral as its predecessor, and in some ways even surpasses it;
- The game has pleasant visuals, a vibrant atmosphere, and well-designed characters;
- The characters are well-written, it's hard to miss;
- Despite the comments about it not being canon, I disagree, because the game's atmosphere and gameplay raise only two questions: "What the hell is going on here?" and "What the hell is going on here?!" (just like in Postal 2);
- There's a story (plot), and it's just as good (again, compared to the previous game);
- Excellent voice acting from the studio "Kurazh-Bambey" and the soundtrack.

Unfortunately, that's where the positives end and the negatives begin:
- The biggest and most significant negative, the only reason I actually gave a negative review, is the INACTION OF THE DEVELOPERS (PUBLISHERS). Postal 3 is a crude game. The number of bugs in it exceeds all standards. Here's a "small" subsection of these bugs:
- Sound bug (the vacuum cleaner sound sometimes gets stuck and goes into a cutscene, sometimes there are creaking sounds, sometimes the music plays in parallel with other music... crazy);
- NPC bug (the poor NPCs are constantly getting stuck somewhere, especially those you have to escort on a mission);
- Achievement bug (some achievements simply don't complete for no apparent reason; restarting the game sometimes helps, but not for long);
- Bug on doors, small objects underfoot, and animals (all of these tend to push the character away with extraordinary force);
- a weapon bug (sometimes the weapon won't fire or an empty catnip can won't be dropped);
- for a 2011 game, I think the game isn't optimized enough;
- the AI ‚Äã‚Äãis terrible; sometimes enemy NPCs can't see each other at point-blank range and just stand there, the same goes for accompanied NPCs;
- constant game crashes (and no, it's not the PC, it's definitely the game, as I've never had a game crash like this before, and my computer isn't weak at all. I'm not the only one with this problem, if you read the comments).

I could mention a few more nuances (for example, the developers' unfulfilled promises), but I think there are already enough downsides to pass judgment.
Again, if the developers had listened to user complaints and fixed their bugs in a timely manner, this game wouldn't be so unplayable. But, obviously, they didn't give a damn about the game, nor about the people who bought it.
Postal 3 reminds me a lot of the Fallout 76 situation, I wonder why, hmmmm...

In the end:
For all the positives I could find, I'd give it a 4/10, and that's a stretch.
I strongly advise against buying this game, as the developers don't deserve it. Even with a discount.

