column9:
[h1]POSTAL 3[/h1]

[u]Pros[/u]

+ Decent weapon variety;
+ Decent environments, as well as their variety;
+ Decent soundtrack.

[u]Cons[/u]

- Weak and boring gameplay;
- Even with the variety, the weapons are boring and you won't use most of them.
- Frequent crashes;
- Very long loading times;
- Low enemy variety;
- Short length (around 5 hours).

[h1]Summary[/h1]

[i]POSTAL 3[/i] is notorious for being hated by fans and [i]Running With Scissors[/i] itself, and I must say they're both completely right to hate it. [i]POSTAL 3[/i] is a game with generic gameplay, where you'll inevitably use only three weapons: the M16, the M60, and the taser, unless you want to kill the enemy in a [i]POSTAL[/i] game. The missions are boring and mostly consist of collecting items/"vehicles" or incapacitating/killing a certain number of enemies‚Äîyes, incapacitating. The game implements a "morality" system that affects the missions and the game's ending. This system completely contradicts what the previous games defined: fun through absurd and comical violence. Finally, the game is short, which may be a blessing in disguise. Excluding all the things [i]POSTAL 3[/i] does poorly, the rest is only decent (barely), and doesn't keep you hooked for long. Even if you're curious about this infamous game, I recommend simply watching a video about it (I recommend [url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLdVzYLjwW0]this video[/url], in English) instead of spending your money, even if it's on sale.

[b]Tell me if the review was helpful or not, and if not, comment why. I appreciate it.[/b]

